annotation.TEXT: Man, this is tricky! Oh, can I make it?
Room 7 fails: 3
Made it! A tiny tap on the down arrow key was all I needed. Okay, now for room 8...
I did a lot of careful duck jumps here, holding down almost continuously throughout.
Room 8 fails: 6
A B-switch? Uh, oh. This can't be good...
Okay, if I do a full stationary duck jump four steps from the top...
I got super nervous with the last couple of jumps here, but fortunately, I didn't screw up.
What horrors upon horrors will I find in room 9?
It's a good thing that you can reach the end from the second-last blue platform in order to be able to do this.
And, I bet there's more...
Now for room 5...
27 attempts later...
All three fails here were due to me holding the down arrow key for just slightly too long while trying to drill stomp through exactly 1 brick at the end. The end result is obvious.
Okay, that wasn't nearly as bad as that first appeared. Now for room 6...
And, there you have it! A perfect clear, after over two dozen fails!
Yep, this nasty-looking room did kill me on occasion, a couple times due to me failing the final tight squeeze, and a couple times due to stupid hasty mistakes.
I barely bumped into the side of the first floating spike thingy as I tried to jump over it (which didn't kill me), and then I landed on it due to the lost momentum (which did).
Aiming for that brick there gives you a little bit more leeway than aiming for the one I broke the first time.
It doesn't look like it should, but I think these horizontal moving platforms are just ever-so-slightly boosting my jump height for some stupid reason.
Last life...
Perfect. Okay, this room is easy.
So, next time, I'll be challenging Dr. Yagokoro in 6-2-2! To be continued... Ze!
Whoa. Okay, I am not jumping off of the red ones, since I get a boost to my jump height if I jump from an upward moving platform, and that's bad here.
My tendency to usually check behind me at the start of a level has revealed a star that otherwise could've been missed.
Oh, god. What is this?
Just like the first time I was here, I carefully disposed of all three Boos and then made my way through, only without having one dumb missed jump this time.
Of course, I can go and fail the tricky jumps even without Boos harassing me.
Aw, nuts... I was standing on air there as long as I held left, and when I released left, I fell.
Clark!
Oh, what the pudding was that? Marisa didn't run across that one-tile gap, and I thought I was moving fast enough horizontally... Ugh...
Okay, what craziness will room 7 contain?
Whoa. Okay, that works I guess, and I'll just ignore those last 3 stars, since this is no longer a perfect run.
I don't think it's possible to even die in this room aside from time up. And, besides that, the only other way to fail would be to hit Koakuma before getting the last 20 stars.
Okay, so we're doing some platforming here, and I can't fall or go too high.
Room 4 fails: 4
Room 2 fails: 0
Yep, looks like a short platforming challenge, followed by a checkpoint, then another short platforming challenge, and so on.
How did I make it through that mess? Well, I'm not complaining!
Woo! Okay, that was a great way to make that jump!
No moving platforms at all...? Hmm...
Now, can I manage to do this all without dying?
Whoa, man!
Room 6 fails: 6
Yeah, this room murdered me a lot. Fortunately, I found a sure-fire way to safely land on the last blue platform. Just do a full running jump onto it from the right.
Oh, these platforms go high enough to impale me on the ceiling spikes if I don't disembark in time.
Room 1 fails: 1
Well, there's a Boo, which I will take the time to kill right now.
Well, that sucked. I obviously didn't want to jump too high there, but I didn't quite jump high enough... Man, that's gonna be really tricky!
Oh! The goal!
Hello, and welcome back to Super Marisa World! Last time, I dealt with a lunatic rabbit.
Me getting through this room flawlessly the first time must've been a fluke. I kept screwing up here, including 3 runs in a row at one point, which annoyed me greatly.
Room 3 fails: 6
Yeah, I did fail this easier-than-it-looks room once.
Okay, so apparently, doing a full running jump from the first yellow platform here gives you just enough height to hit your head on the ceiling spikes.
Oh, BTW, I discovered this recently by accident. If you hold the right shift key while on the map, you can see your high score and best special score for the level you're on.
Also, the remaining 20 stars are right here, which means I've found every star! (The three I didn't collect were the ones under the last blue platform in room 3.)
Room 10 fails: 0
Yep, that's right! This is the first time I reached room 9 on a currently perfect run.
David!
I really hope I won't encounter a fourth Boo, or this could get really annoying.
DEFINITELY do a duck jump for that last jump there! Two of my fails were to the ceiling spikes on that last jump.
Oh, Lord Helix...
Now, let's begin the second half of world 6, with 6-2-1!
What in the world...?
Yeah, I guess you have to go as far as the fourth brick in order to lure out the last Boo.
Delano!
Oh, geez. What's the challenge here in room 4?
Room 9 fails: 0
This is the only room (besides the goal room) that I've never died in, and I've gotten good at getting through it fairly quickly.
After some of my fails here, I used my remaining lives to practice this room and try to figure out the most reliable way to get through it. Even then, I failed here a lot.
Oh, wow. I took my horizontal momentum into account and managed to make it through that tight squeeze.
Whoa, whoa, whoa! I almost clicked "No" for preserving the replay there! That would've been bad!
A checkpoint already? ...Is this level going to consist of several short platforming challenges with a checkpoint in between each one?
Yep, I was right. I'd definitely rather just kill them on the safe land to the left, instead of worrying about trying to evade them while making tricky jumps.
Oh, god... A blue platform... Please no Hammer Brothers...
Okay, I guess there were only 3 Boos. Well, here comes room 10, and there's still 20 stars at large, so I probably still have a few more rooms to go, and with only 1 life left...
Room 5 fails: 1
...Or is it? I can't do that same thing for this one. I'll have to carefully drill stomp through exactly one brick...
(Apparently, Harry Truman was given a middle initial, but no actual middle name.)
BTW, there wouldn't happen to be a third Boo in this room, would there?
Yep, there is. I'm going to lure it to the left and kill it just like with the first two.
I guess this is kinda neat, and helpful if you haven't gotten 100 Special Score on some levels and want to go back and try to perfect them.
